    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Genome and Creationism</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Arthur L Yeager letter on June 27 article holds mapping of genome and links between human DNA and DNA of all living things refute theory of creationism</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The now complete mapping of the genome (June 27), coupled with scientific findings of an almost total congruence between human DNA and the DNA of all living things, should, at last, put to rest any serious consideration of creationism.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The now complete mapping of the genome (June 27), coupled with scientific findings of an almost total congruence between human DNA and the DNA of all living things, should, at last, put to rest any serious consideration of creationism.</p>
        <p>Let those who continue to so believe enjoy their fairy tales.</p>
        <p>DR. ARTHUR L. YEAGER  Edison, N.J.</p>
      </block>
